com.azure.messaging.eventhubs.models

Class PartitionContext

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.azure.messaging.eventhubs.models.PartitionContext

  • public class PartitionContext
extends Object
    A model class to contain partition information that will be provided to each instance of PartitionProcessor.

    • Constructor Detail

      • PartitionContext

        public PartitionContext(String partitionId,
                        String eventHubName,
                        String consumerGroup,
                        String ownerId,
                        String eTag,
                        PartitionManager partitionManager)
        Creates an instance of PartitionContext that contains partition information available to each PartitionProcessor.
        Parameters:
        partitionId - The partition id of the partition processed by the PartitionProcessor.
        eventHubName - The Event Hub name associated with the EventProcessor.
        consumerGroup - The consumer group name associated with the EventProcessor.
        ownerId - The unique identifier of the EventProcessor instance.
        eTag - The last known ETag stored in PartitionManager for this partition.
        partitionManager - A PartitionManager implementation to read and update partition ownership and checkpoint information.

      • updateCheckpoint

        public Mono<Void> updateCheckpoint(EventData eventData)
        Updates the checkpoint for this partition using the event data. This will serve as the last known successfully processed event in this partition if the update is successful.
        Parameters:
        eventData - The event data to use for updating the checkpoint.
        Returns:
        a representation of deferred execution of this call.

      • updateCheckpoint

        public Mono<Void> updateCheckpoint(long sequenceNumber,
                                   Long offset)
        Updates a checkpoint using the given offset and sequence number. This will serve as the last known successfully processed event in this partition if the update is successful.
        Parameters:
        sequenceNumber - The sequence number to update the checkpoint.
        offset - The offset to update the checkpoint.
        Returns:
        a representation of deferred execution of this call.
